# Conventions (Migration Phase)

# Full conventions apply after all migration tasks are complete.

# See conventions.md for target architecture.

## Path aliases (current tsconfig.json)

- `components/*` → `components/*`
- `features/*` → `features/*`
- `graphql/*` → `graphql/*`
- `locales/*` → `locales/*`
- `lib/*` → `lib/*`
- `styles/*` → `styles/*`
- `themes/*` → `themes/*` (will move to `lib/` after structure cleanup)
- `enums/*` → `enums/*`
- `types/*` → `../types/*` (shared with server — do not move)

## TypeScript

- Prefer `z.infer<typeof schema>` over hand-written duplicates.
- Never use `any` type — always use explicit TypeScript types (e.g. `React.ReactNode`, `unknown`, or `z.infer<typeof schema>`).
- Shared domain types in root `types/` (shared with server — do not move).
- Feature-only types in `feature/types/`.
- Barrel-export public modules via `index.ts`.

## Imports & style

- Remove unused imports from every file you modify before finishing a task.
- After deleting files, remove any resulting empty directories before finishing a task.
- Order: external → alias → relative.
- Use `cn()` for conditional classes; CVA for component variants.
- Toast feedback: `sonner` via `@/components/custom-ui/message` — don't duplicate in components.
- i18n: `const { t } = useTranslations()`; keys as dot-paths (`'feature.label'`).
- Never hardcode display strings — always go through `t()`.

## Styles (transition phase)

- Existing components: keep scss unchanged — do not refactor.
- New components: Tailwind CSS + cn() only.
- Do not mix scss and Tailwind in the same new component.
- scss will be fully replaced by Tailwind in a future refactor.
- For layout or positioning fixes (e.g. `next/image` `fill` parent), use Tailwind utility classes — do not use inline `style` props on wrapper or image elements.

## Folder structure (current)

- Colocate by feature under `features/`.
- Promote to root only when reused across multiple features.
- Keep `server/`, `types/`, `docker/` untouched.
- Keep code close to where it is used. Prefer feature-level and route-level colocation over centralized abstraction.
- GraphQL: all related concerns must be colocated in the nearest feature or route folder inside a single `queries.ts` file. This includes:
  - GraphQL query document
  - queryKey definition
  - Zod schema for runtime validation
- Zustand stores: define in the consuming Client Component file, directly above the component. Only extract to a shared frontend `store/` directory when reused by multiple features or routes.
- components/ inside a route folder contains only UI components, no state or schema logic

## Zustand (available now)

- Small flat stores with `setX` actions; selector syntax: `useStore((s) => s.field)`.
- Never store server data in Zustand.

## Do not

- Move or restructure `server/`, `types/`, `docker/`.
- Restructure internals of `features/` or `components/`.
- Fetch in `useEffect`.
- Hardcode display strings — always use `t()`.
- Create default-export utility modules (except Next.js pages).
- Add new Context — use Zustand when client state is needed.
- Use Apollo Client for new code — graphql-request + RQ migration is planned.
- Duplicate toast logic in components.
- Put API response data in Zustand or React state.
- Skip Zod validation on API responses.
- Refactor existing scss — leave it for future Tailwind migration.
- Only change what is necessary to complete this task.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.
- Do not use inline `style` for layout or positioning fixes — use Tailwind utility classes instead.
